   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">The independent static bypass switch (ISBS) is an option for systems
with a bypass and a manual bypass switch. It provides a backup for
the automatic transfer to static bypass in case the main controller
cannot turn on the static switch EN.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">The ISBS monitors the system output in case the main controller
is inoperable and can switch to static bypass if needed. When the
switch over to static bypass is triggered by the ISBS it is also called
ISBS operation. In ISBS operation the system is locked in static bypass.
The switch over is automatic without any interruption to the load.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">To indicate the status of the ISBS two optional relays can be added <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(K701)</b> and <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(K702)</b>. They are used to signal:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">The overall status of the ISBS.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">If the ISBS have triggered and switch over the system to ISBS
operation.</p>
            </li>
         </ul>The same information can also be seen on the board. The status
and activation of the ISBS is also indicated by the LEDs STATUS_2
and STATUS_3 respectively. For more detailed information of the LEDs
on the board see <xref href="Bruce_Troubleshoot_the_ISBS_CPT_0000916510.dita"
